http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/%E2%80%98Training-the-trainers%E2%80%99-programme/article13991832.ece

The National Institute for Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises (Ni-MSME) will be organising a two-week workshop in association with Abhaya, an NGO, on ‘Training the trainers in entrepreneurship development (TOT-ED)’ from January 18.There is no entry fee. The workshop will be held at Samata College in MVP Colony.The programme is aimed at training officers of NGOs and staff of various colleges and institutions holding post-graduate degree in commerce, management, or engineering.For more details about the programme, email:profashionift@gmail.com, or call 9000938831.